Notes:
1. all the ressources produced will come with an open licence, mainly (L)GPL for
source code, creative commons BY SA for documentation, "artistic" and other
material. For external bits used (e.g. hardware), an effort will be made to use
the most open solution possible, but while keeping some pragmatism. For example,
if the pcduino3 platform will prove to fit our needs and / or be the cheapest
solution available, we will stick with it even if it's not the most ope
platform. If a realist drop-in candidate for replacement emerges, we will
evaluate the possibility of changing.
